snippet.textDisplay:
There is this low budget movie called SEAL Patrol (2014) and getting the combat right was important to them, AND there is also a good amount of vfx in the last half, so it seems right up your league to react to!!
(This movie ain't great. I know one of the actors in the movie, and he's awesome and the guys at the heart of it mean well, but it was made with no budget as sort of a "let's all go to Utah and shoot some guns, Boys!" It was originally called Blackjacks since it's a team of retired special forces and they're CALLED the Blackjacks, but some production company or distributor said "Change the name to SEAL patrol, sounds more military group." while none of them were seals, nor do they patrol. lol)
